*fmod*

(PHP 4 >= 4.2.0, PHP 5, PHP 7)

fmod â€” Returns the floating point remainder (modulo) of the division of the
arguments

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  fmod ( float $x , float $y ) : float~

Returns the floating point remainder of dividing the dividend ({x}) by the
divisor ({y}). The remainder (r) is defined as: x = i * y + r, for some integer
i. If {y} is non-zero, r has the same sign as {x} and a magnitude less than the
magnitude of {y}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{x}

  The dividend

{y}

  The divisor

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The floating point remainder of {x}/{y}

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 Using fmod()

<?php >
  $x = 5.7;
  $y = 1.3;
  $r = fmod($x, $y);
  // $r equals 0.5, because 4 * 1.3 + 0.5 = 5.7
<?>

